<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I respectfully disagree with a previous message regarding "never to fear" MOBs while fighting in groups.  I do agree that often it is unwise to fear during dungeon fights, since the feared MOB can bring back a train after the spell wears off.  However, in wide open areas, fear can often save other group members' lives or at least reduce the damage they take.  For example, while fighting treants or druids in the Karanas, I often fear away a new spawn during the middle of a combat.  This serves 2 purposes.  First, it prevents the new spawn from assisting the MOB that the group is already fighting.  Second, it breaks up the spawn time so the group doesn't face multiple enemies at one time.<br>
Another comment I have is the importance of making "/pet back off" a hotkey.  It has saved my life and my groups' lives many times when I called off my pet in the following situations to defend me or other party members:<br>
1) A new spawn or 2nd MOB aggroed on me while the group (and my pet) is fighting another MOB.<br>
2) Another caster (especially the healer) is getting attacked by a 2nd MOB, so I send my pet to protect him/her.<br>
3) A MOB is feared to break up spawn and pet gave chase.  (recall pet to save its life)<br>
4) Wrong targeting sent the pet to attack the wrong NPC (a high level city guard, for example)<p>

So Keep on FEARING and control your pets will, my fellow evil brothers and sisters :)</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
